  "prompt": "If my ATM card is blocked for online transactions then how do i restart it?",
  "response": "To restart online transactions on your ATM card, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. Contact your bank directly\n- Call customer service\n- Visit a local branch\n- Use internet banking/mobile banking app\n\n2. Verify your identity\n- Provide necessary personal details\n- Confirm your account information\n- Answer security questions\n\n3. Request online transaction activation\n- Explain that you want to unblock online transactions\n- Confirm your intention to resume digital payments\n\n4. Additional methods\n- Some banks allow self-service unblocking through:\n  - Online banking portal\n  - Mobile banking app\n  - Net banking\n  - ATM\n\n5. Possible requirements\n- Provide a valid reason for blocking\n- Update KYC documents\n- Verify recent transactions\n- Confirm your current contact details\n\n6. Alternative options\n- Request a new card\n- Reset transaction permissions\n- Perform online verification\n\nThe exact process might vary depending on your specific bank's policies. It's best to directly contact your bank's customer service for precise guidance tailored to your account.\n\nRemember to keep your bank's contact information handy for such situations.",
